title: Michigan State University Road Race
description: Second annual MSU Cycling Git TUFF MWCCC road race.
course:
This is the race for all the tough guys and gals out
there. Flat, exposed 4.4 mile loop on country roads near Dansville, MI. But flat
doesn\\\\\\\'t necessarily mean boring--strong spring winds should help to ensure that
the racing is hard and the pain level high. And that\\\\\\\'s not all: the loop includes 1.2 miles of dirt road, to keep things interesting and select for a worthy winner.
registration: Opens at 8:30 am. Entry fee is $12 per rider. All racers must show a valid collegiate license in order to race. One day licenses will be available.
notes:
Because of the dirt section on this course, STURDY WHEELS AND TIRES are
recommended. This is a “good quality” dirt road, and you can certainly ride
standard road equipment, but you should probably save the carbon rims and
ultralite tires for another day.
Yellow line rule in effect at all times. If there is no yellow line, then you must
stay on the right half of the road. Follow vehicles will be provided.
directions:
Registration and parking will be at Dansville High School. From
East Lansing/Okemos, take Grand River Ave/M43 to Meridian Rd. Go SOUTH
on Meridian for about 11 miles until you reach M36. Turn LEFT to go EAST on
M36. Drive on M36 for about 2.5 miles until you reach the small town of Dansville. Turn RIGHT onto Adams Street and follow that into the school. For an online map, see: http://tinyurl.com/3bqff2. Please note that WE WILL NOT
BE STARTING OR STAGING THE RACES AT THE SCHOOL; the staging will be at the start/finish line approximately 1.5 miles away (see maps below). There is no place to park at the start/finish, so if you want to watch other races, ride your
bike there.
